      <opener>
        <salute>Dear Sir, </salute>
      </opener>
      <p>Mr. Takahata, Manager of Messrs. Suzuki Company of London advised me today that you have been kind enough to buy several fine pictures for me, and I beg to hasten to tender you my best thanks for all troubles. I beg to mention that I deeply appreciate your kind offices for me, when you are so busy always. </p>
      <p>I beg to ask you, availing on this opportunity how the bronze castings are going on and beg to mention that it would give me a great pleasure to hear about their progress and other news. </p>
      <p>Thanking you for your kindness once more and with my best wishes for the meanwhile, </p>
      <p>I am, dear Sir, </p>
      <closer>
        <salute>Yours faithfully, </salute>
        <signed>Kojiro Matsukata</signed>
      </closer>
      <postscript>
        <p>PS [manuscrit] : Your aimable daughter and friend are all well with M. Hatori has called upon you. </p>
      </postscript>
